{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"32348a1c-b04a-5384-9802-a632799904bd","html":"<p>Flexbox is a must in today‚Äôs UI development world as it lets you create responsive and elegant layouts in record time üôÜ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è  </p>\n<p>We‚Äôll go through concrete examples one at at time and build the following <a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/MdyQJE\">UI</a> containing a navbar and a list of cards.  </p>\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center\">\n<img class=\"article-img\" alt=\"render of the component mentioned\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15229355/57548653-cd9ab180-7361-11e9-9820-00ddda69e799.png\">\n</div>\n<p>Throughout each step, we‚Äôll learn essential Flexbox concepts to get you going on the right foot, so feel free to create your own <a href=\"https://codepen.io/\">codepen</a> to try them out.</p>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"learning-the-basics-with-a-navbar\"><a href=\"#learning-the-basics-with-a-navbar\" aria-label=\"learning the basics with a navbar permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Learning the basics with a navbar</h2>\n<p>Our HTML will look something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>nav</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>#<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>https://image.flaticon.com/icons/svg/145/145867.svg<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>#<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Home<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>#<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Blog<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>nav</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>With an icon to the left and two links to the right, pretty standard stuff.</p>\n<p>This navbar will use three Flexbox concepts: <code class=\"language-text\">display</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">justify-content</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">align-items</code>, so let‚Äôs cover them one by one.</p>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"display\"><a href=\"#display\" aria-label=\"display permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>display</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">nav</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The first thing you‚Äôll type when working with Flexbox. It makes it so that every child of our <code class=\"language-text\">nav</code> takes advantage of the flex context.<br>\nWe can now start moving around the container‚Äôs children.</p>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"justify-content\"><a href=\"#justify-content\" aria-label=\"justify content permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>justify-content</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">nav</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">justify-content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex-start | flex-end | center | space-between | space-around | space-evenly<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>It determines where we place our container‚Äôs elements on the main axis.<br>\nEach one is pretty self explanatory but it‚Äôs worth playing around with it.</p>\n<p>In our case, we want our items to be on the right (the end) of the navbar:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">nav</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">justify-content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex-end<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>‚ÄúBut Chris, by using the value <code class=\"language-text\">flex-end</code> <strong>everything</strong> goes to the end of my container, even the icon !‚Äù, and you‚Äôre absolutely right, we want our icon to be on the left while everything else is on the right. To do so, we can use a pretty neat trick, we set the icon‚Äôs <code class=\"language-text\">margin-right</code> to auto, telling our layout to automatically place the icon to the far left like so.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token comment\">/* Target the first link in our navbar (the icon)  */</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">nav > a:first-child</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">margin-right</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> auto<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Everything is starting to look better, although we still need to center our icon vertically.</p>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"align-items\"><a href=\"#align-items\" aria-label=\"align items permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>align-items</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">nav</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">align-items</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> stretch | flex-start | flex-end | center | baseline<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>It determines the position of the container‚Äôs children on the cross axis (the axis perpendicular to the one used by <code class=\"language-text\">justify-content</code>).</p>\n<p>In our case, we want to align our navbar items vertically, like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">nav</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">justify-content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex-end<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">align-items</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And that‚Äôs it, we have a fully fledged navbar and we learned three essential concepts of Flexbox ! üéâ</p>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"bonus-flex-direction\"><a href=\"#bonus-flex-direction\" aria-label=\"bonus flex direction permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Bonus: flex-direction</h3>\n<p>Even though we‚Äôre not using it here, I think it‚Äôs worth mentioning <code class=\"language-text\">flex-direction</code>. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.container</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">flex-direction</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> row | row-reverse | column | column-reverse<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Just like its name entails, it determines the container‚Äôs main axis, think of it as creating a horizontal (by default) or vertical layout.</p>\n<p>Try it out ! You‚Äôll see that defining it as <code class=\"language-text\">column</code> will have the expected result: a vertical layout.</p>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"going-a-bit-further-with-a-card-list\"><a href=\"#going-a-bit-further-with-a-card-list\" aria-label=\"going a bit further with a card list permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Going a bit further with a card list</h2>\n<p>Alright, you may have seen the <a href=\"https://codepen.io/christopherkade/pen/MdyQJE\">example UI</a> shared earlier, we‚Äôll now work on creating this card layout and have it be responsive (which is made very easy thanks to Flexbox).</p>\n<p>Here what our HTML will look like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>article</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>card-container<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>card<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>card-link<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>#<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>       \n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>May 4, 2019 | 3 min read<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h2</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>card-title<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>My awesome card<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>card-description<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>...with a description !<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n  <span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- More cards below --></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>article</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We will display a large amount of cards on <strong>multiple lines</strong>, these can be articles (like on <a href=\"https://christopherkade.com/blog\">christopherkade.com</a>), TODOs or anything you‚Äôd like.</p>\n<p>To do so, we only need one new concept: <code class=\"language-text\">flex-wrap</code>.</p>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"flex-wrap\"><a href=\"#flex-wrap\" aria-label=\"flex wrap permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>flex-wrap</h3>\n<p>It tells our container to wrap its items onto multiple lines when needed. By default <code class=\"language-text\">flex</code> will fit every item on the same line.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.card-container</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">flex-wrap</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> nowrap | wrap | wrap-reverse<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>So, our <code class=\"language-text\">.card-container</code> will now look like the following:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.card-container</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">flex-wrap</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> wrap<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">justify-content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Try moving your window‚Äôs size around, it‚Äôs responsive and will render the the amount of cards that can fit each line automatically.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"wait-thats-it\"><a href=\"#wait-thats-it\" aria-label=\"wait thats it permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Wait, that‚Äôs it?</h2>\n<p>Yeah, it‚Äôs not hard to get started with Flexbox. Of course there‚Äôs much more to it, but that‚Äôs more than enough to produce cool layouts.</p>\n<p>If you want to go further, make sure to check out CSS-Trick‚Äôs <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/\">Complete Guide to Flexbox</a> which was the main inspiration to write this post.</p>\n<p>Of course, if you have any questions concerning Flexbox, CSS as a whole or Javascript, don‚Äôt hesitate to send them to me on Twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/christo_kade\">@christo_kade</a> üòÑ</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/flexbox","tagSlugs":["/tag/css/","/tag/design/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-05-10","description":"Easy, responsive and elegant.","tags":["CSS","Design"],"title":"Flexbox 101"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/flexbox"}}